## COMPREHENSIVE PACKAGE STRUCTURE & CONFIGURATION ANALYSIS

Based on my thorough exploration of the AI SDK provider packages, here's a complete breakdown of the boilerplate needed to create a new provider package:

---

### 1. PACKAGE FILE STRUCTURE

**Small Provider Package Layout (e.g., `@ai-sdk/fireworks`):**

```
packages/fireworks/
├── src/
│   ├── index.ts                          (main export file)
│   ├── version.ts                        (version injection)
│   ├── {provider}-provider.ts            (factory & interface)
│   ├── {provider}-provider.test.ts       (provider tests)
│   ├── {model-type}-model.ts             (model implementation)
│   ├── {model-type}-model.test.ts        (model tests)
│   ├── {model-type}-options.ts           (model options & types)
│   ├── {model-type}-settings.ts          (model IDs & configs)
│   └── [other-model-types...]
├── package.json                          (npm configuration)
├── tsconfig.json                         (TypeScript config)
├── tsconfig.build.json                   (build-specific config)
├── tsup.config.ts                        (build tool config)
├── turbo.json                            (monorepo task config)
├── vitest.node.config.js                 (Node test config)
├── vitest.edge.config.js                 (Edge test config)
├── README.md                             (provider documentation)
├── CHANGELOG.md                          (version history)
└── [potentially: vitest.browser.config.js for browser tests]
